{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/write-better-stories-with-this-python-tool-ad1371158822", "time": 1683002876.880707, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/write-better-stories-with-this-python-tool-ad1371158822/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Write Better Stories with this Python Tool | by Favio V\u00e1zquez | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Write Better Stories with this Python Tool", "description": "If you write articles, blog posts or reports to your boss a lot, then you want to make sure people are understanding what you say. In this article, I\u2019ll show how to use a Python library called\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://github.com/shivam5992/textstat", "anchor_text": "textstat", "paragraph_index": 0}], "all_paragraphs": ["If you write articles, blog posts or reports to your boss a lot, then you want to make sure people are understanding what you say. In this article, I\u2019ll show how to use a Python library called textstat to determine readability, complexity, grade level and more about your text.", "You can easily install textstat via the Python Package Index (PyPI):", "You can also install the latest version from GitHub:", "There are a lot of useful functions in the library to:", "The basic idea of the library is for you to write a text and then run the different tests and indices to see how good is your text. I will explain how to do it in the examples below.", "I will take a piece from an older article I wrote and then run the different tests upon it. The article is:", "And the text I\u2019ll be using is this:", "Data science is the main focus of most sciences and studies right now, it needs a lot of things like AI, programming, statistics, business understanding, effective presentation skills and much more. That\u2019s why it\u2019s not easy to understand or study. But we can do it, we are doing it.", "Data science has become the standard solving problem framework for academia and the industry and it\u2019s going to be like that for a while. But we need to remember where we are coming from, who we are and where we are going.", "In this GitHub repo you\u2019ll find the next notebook running the library:", "There\u2019s also something interesting I discovered creating this code. How you can run every method of a class in Python. I didn\u2019t find it online so here it is with the example of this library:", "Pretty cool. But something was missing, what about spelling? There are great libraries for that in Python, but autocorrect is the easiest one to use:", "As you can see I intentionally misspelled the words presentation, focus, and framework, and with this simple piece of code I can fix it:", "Hopefully, you can use this to write better articles, reports and much more if you are a Python user. Please let me know what you think below :)", "You can also contact me through Instagram/Twitter:", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Data scientist, physicist and computer engineer. Love sharing ideas, thoughts and contributing to Open Source in Machine Learning and Deep Learning ;)."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fad1371158822&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fwrite-better-stories-with-this-python-tool-ad1371158822&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fwrite-better-stories-with-this-python-tool-ad1371158822&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_l